<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
     As a paladin PC, I hate having to waste 10, 15, 20 minutes or longer begging for a bind.  This is especially bad during the early hours.  I suggest that an NPC merchant be placed in each town, (or the Priest of Discord would work as well) to whom I can go and purchase a bind.  Say for a cost of 10 to 20 pp I can be on my way in no time.  The somewhat nominal cost would make the convienance of the merchant a luxury and still enable PC's to try and get binds cheaper from other players.  Anyone agree on this? 
</FONT>
