<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I think one aspect of paying for binds has been missed by everyone.  If players can buy binds from NPC's then binders lose one of the services they can sell to other players.<P>If you could buy any magic ring you wanted in any town you visited, then would anyone ever take the time to become jewelers?  Would any player buy their jewelry if they did?<P>I understand that binders often do not charge.  But requireing players to get bound from other players means that player-to-player interaction is generated.  Buy from NPCs in contrasts moves players to becomeing soloers.<P><P>------------------<BR>I am me,<BR>  <BR>Aieee!
