<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
 <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by yrogerg:<BR><B>I guess i'm one of those pesterers. I don't know what else to do, i must get a bind when i go to  a new city. There were times when i just got tired of waiting and went out fighting, but that always ends up in me getting killed and spending all night getting back my stuff. This in turn leads to more pestering for SoWs or TPs. I would rather be able to fend for myself, but theres nothing else i can do. What's a good rate for tp anyway? I have always ended up getting free ones in the past, but i don't like mooching</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Why not try making friends with several Druids and Shamans? <P>If you have true friends in the server, then it's not considered pestering. A real friend will bind or sow you for free, just for the asking. <P>Why bother strangers and beg (or pay) them for Binds when you can ask your friend:<P>"hey buddy, I see you're in the same zone as me, can you spare a minute to bind me please?"<P>The lesson here? <P>Make friends in Everquest. Making friends is the single most important skill you will learn in EQ. <P>If you have lots of friends, you will always have free binds and buffs and SOWs everywhere, and anywhere you go. And you will never feel guilty about mooching off anyone, because friends will always do these things gladly and for free. <BR>
</FONT>
