<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well, making friends is fine and dandy as long as they're on, and in the same zone.  After travelling to Neriak, where getting a bind is a non-issue because of the massive amount of casters always milling around the entrance tunnel, and getting a bind before heading to Guk, I returned to Kunark.  Now, the last time I did this, I completely forgot about getting a bind until I was PK'ed in the Frontier Mountains and found myself back in Neriak.<P>This is a VERY long walk back, just because of the necessity of using boats.<P>This time, I remembered that I needed a bind (only after seeing someone refer to it on guildchat) while I was camping Kwinn in Friona Vie (PKland).  So I headed back into Cabilis to get my bind, and go back to camping.  Well.  There were a total of 5 people in east cabilis and I was by myself in west cabilis.  Of those 5, 1 lvl 10 monk, 1 lvl 10 shaman, and 3 anonymous dudes.  I got no response from my '/ooc looking for a bind at the bank, will pay'.  All of my friends were a minimum 3 zones away, more than I'm willing to pull them out of their way.<P>End result?  I logged out for the night.  Just one more annoyance with the game (they're building).  Oh, and I didn't get one rare spawn the entire 3 nights I spent in guk.  yay me.<P>Btw, I play on Tallon Zek, where quests have the added 'feature' of sending me deep into the heart of the other races.  Damn that shackle of bronze for being a minor lightsource.  The only effect it has is to make me stand out like a lit christmas tree during the night.  Not the wisest thing for PK...
</FONT>
